          MODULE=kipi-plugins
         VERSION=5.3.0
          SOURCE=digikam-$VERSION.tar.xz
      SOURCE_URL=http://download.kde.org/stable/digikam/
SOURCE_DIRECTORY=$BUILD_DIRECTORY/digikam-$VERSION
      SOURCE_VFY=sha256:b36cfa27278936d41ab5f33c99fe9ccdfd545eada3e1e32efe9f9e3fdf2c3e5c
   MODULE_PREFIX=${KDE4_INSTALL_DIR:-/usr}
        WEB_SITE=http://projects.kde.org/projects/extragear/graphics/kipi-plugins
         ENTERED=20090318
         UPDATED=20161107
           SHORT="KDE Image Plugin Interface"

cat << EOF
digiKam makes use of KIPI plugins for lots of added functionality. KIPI
(KDE Image Plugin Interface) is an initiative to create a common plugin
infrastructure for digiKam, KimDaBa, Showimg, and GwenView. Its aim is
to allow development of image plugins which can shared among KDE
graphical applications.

Note: This is the digikam tarball and is setup to only to compile and install
kipi-plugins. If you have digikam installed this module is not required.
EOF
